SECONDARY VAMPIRE

Secondary Vampires are MDC undead created when a Master Vampire drains a
victim completely and chooses to transform rather than kill them.  They retain
their intelligence and personality but are bound by the same limitations as
all vampires.  On Rifts Earth, vampire kingdoms exist in Mexico and other
regions, where Secondary Vampires serve as soldiers and operatives.

ATTRIBUTES (approximate ranges):
  IQ: 3-18   ME: 3-18   MA: 4-24   PS: 12-32 (Supernatural)
  PP: 7-22   PE: 11-26  PB: 4-24   Spd: 8-28

DAMAGE POOL:
  MDC: 3d6 x10 + 40 (approx 70-220 MDC)
  HP: PE + 2d6

SPECIAL ABILITIES:
  - MDC body: immune to SDC/HP weapons
  - Supernatural Physical Strength and Endurance
  - Rapid regeneration of MDC damage
  - Hypnotic gaze: can mesmerize victims
  - Immunity to normal (non-silver, non-magic) weapons

PENALTIES:
  - Not OCC eligible
  - Sunlight: takes 2d6 MDC per melee round of exposure
  - Wild fire (burning wood, torches): double MDC damage
  - Cannot enter a dwelling without an invitation
  - Stake through the heart: instant death

OCC ELIGIBLE: No.
ALIGNMENT: Any (most vampires are evil, but Secondary Vampires vary).

See also: wild_vampire, werewolf, races
